        <h1>LastTweetPNG.com</h1>
        <p>LastTweetPNG.com provides a super-simple API to display your latest tweet as an image.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="row">
        <h2>How to do it...</h2>
        <p>Add <code>http://www.lasttweetpng.com/:username/tweet/latest.png</code> to your <code>img</code> tag in your HTML, where <code>:username</code> is your twitter username.</p>
        <p>Example: This code, <code>&lt;img src="http://lasttweetpng.com/joshfinnie/tweet/last.png" alt=""&gt;</code>, produces this image:</p>
        <p class="text-center"><img src="http://lasttweetpng.com/joshfinnie/tweet/last.png" alt=""></p>
